Program: Outlook
Title: Iraqi Children and Depleted Uranium
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbqyj
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Report from an Iraqi hospital on the children being born with deformities which have been blamed on the use of depleted uranium by allies in the Gulf war. Also, young Indians rediscovering their roots with classical Indian dancing, an archaeological find of an 4000 year old oak tree circle in England and, why an Italian man and woman were prevented from kissing in the centre of Florence. Show less